<H3> <TI>   Rising Costs of Consumer Goods, Services Examined </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rising Costs of Consumer Goods, Services Examined </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1428B VECHERNIY ALMATY in Russian 16 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1428B </F>
<F P=104>  VECHERNIY ALMATY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article under "Gorstat Reports" rubric: "On </F>
the Change in the Prices for Consumer Goods and Paid Services in 
the First Four Months of 1994"] 
  [Text] The prices for 
consumer goods and services continue to rise. 
  They are rising faster for foodstuffs and have tripled since 
the beginning of the year. For nonfood products, they increased 
by a factor of 2.7. The cost of a selection of food items made 
up of 33 vitally necessary products rose by a factor of 2.7 in 
April in comparison with December and amounted to 427 tenge. 
  The largest increase in consumer prices was registered for 
dairy products (by a factor of 7.2), which increased in price as 
follows: milk by a factor of 5.5, cream and sour cream by 10, 
curds by 9.6, eggs by 5.6, poultry by 4.9, and mutton by a 
factor of 4.3. 
  There was a noticeable increase in the cost of nonfood 
products: clothing and footwear by a factor of 2.7, office 
supplies by 6.1, and refrigerators, washing machines, and 
televisions by a factor of 2. The prices for medical compounds 
increased by a factor of 4.5. 
  All kinds of paid services became more expensive. There was 
a 
sharp increase in prices in April. For the first four months of 
the year, the prices for passenger transport services increased 
by a factor of 4.5, services of a legal nature and for banking 
institutions by 5.6, housing services by 5.2, and paid public 
health services by a factor of 3.9. 
  For the first four months of 1994, the index of the change 
in 
consumer prices, which in international practice is considered 
to be an indicator of inflation, amounted to 294.1 percent for 
the city of Almaty. 

</TEXT>

